Installing SystemConfidence

To configure the low-latency timers in ORB, run:

scripts/config.sh <target>

Where <target> is one of:
    x86cluster -- generic x86-64
    crayxt     -- Cray XT      
    ibmbgp     -- IBM BG/P    
    sicortex   -- SiCortex   
    power7     -- IBM Power7

Create or copy a make.inc from the 'examples' subdirectory to set up
appropriate make variables. 'make.inc.generic' is a good starting
point. Then simply:

make

This will produce a 'sysconfidence' executable.
